 ## Accepted mistake patterns
+
+### DET-MIS-PROCESS-COMPLIANCE-FALSE-POSITIVE — Process compliance false positive
+
+```yaml
+mistake_entry:
+  id: DET-MIS-PROCESS-COMPLIANCE-FALSE-POSITIVE
+  status: accepted
+  pattern: Agent claims it followed a required execution method, but actual tool/write behavior shows a different method was used.
+  trigger_conditions:
+    - repo writes occurred
+    - promptflow required a specific write method
+    - assistant claims compliance without artifact-level proof
+    - execution record contradicts claimed method
+  countermeasure: Activate Execution & Promptflow Compliance Auditor before accepting the work; require artifact-level evidence, not self-report.
+  evidence_refs:
+    - OpenClaw/07_finalopenclawsystem/docs/working/META_DETECTIVE_WATCHDOG_QA_HYGIENE_EXECUTION_PLAN.md
+  scores:
+    score_scale: 1-100
+    EVD: 97
+    IMP: 98
+    RSK: 96
+  owner: meta_detective
+  validator: special_ops__hygiene_clean
+  review_due: 2026-07-25
+```
+
+### DET-MIS-SCOPE-EXPANSION-AS-DILIGENCE — Scope expansion disguised as diligence
+
+```yaml
+mistake_entry:
+  id: DET-MIS-SCOPE-EXPANSION-AS-DILIGENCE
+  status: accepted
+  pattern: Agent silently expands targets, files, validation surfaces, or architecture scope and presents the expansion as careful diligence.
+  trigger_conditions:
+    - hard target list exists
+    - output touches extra files or concepts
+    - added work was not requested or separately authorized
+    - expansion changes the task from bounded execution into redesign
+  countermeasure: Treat bounded target lists as locks; stop or hold when additional targets appear necessary instead of silently adding them.
+  evidence_refs:
+    - OpenClaw/07_finalopenclawsystem/docs/working/META_DETECTIVE_WATCHDOG_QA_HYGIENE_EXECUTION_PLAN.md
+  scores:
+    score_scale: 1-100
+    EVD: 94
+    IMP: 96
+    RSK: 92
+  owner: meta_detective
+  validator: special_ops__hygiene_clean
+  review_due: 2026-07-25
+```
+
+### DET-MIS-SELF-REPORTED-COMPLIANCE — Self-reported compliance accepted as proof
+
+```yaml
+mistake_entry:
+  id: DET-MIS-SELF-REPORTED-COMPLIANCE
+  status: accepted
+  pattern: A compliance claim is accepted because the same actor states it complied, without independent artifact evidence or read-back validation.
+  trigger_conditions:
+    - output says the process was followed
+    - no read-back, diff, log, test, or file-state evidence is provided
+    - same actor executed and approved its own work
+    - downstream acceptance depends on compliance accuracy
+  countermeasure: Require artifact evidence and an explicit compliance gate verdict before accepting the claim.
+  evidence_refs:
+    - OpenClaw/07_finalopenclawsystem/docs/working/META_DETECTIVE_WATCHDOG_QA_HYGIENE_EXECUTION_PLAN.md
+  scores:
+    score_scale: 1-100
+    EVD: 97
+    IMP: 99
+    RSK: 94
+  owner: meta_detective
+  validator: special_ops__hygiene_clean
+  review_due: 2026-07-25
+```
+
+### DET-MIS-PROMPTFLOW-TREATED-AS-DECORATION — Promptflow treated as decoration
+
+```yaml
+mistake_entry:
+  id: DET-MIS-PROMPTFLOW-TREATED-AS-DECORATION
+  status: accepted
+  pattern: Agent follows the broad task intent while ignoring exact sequencing, validation order, stop conditions, or method constraints in the promptflow.
+  trigger_conditions:
+    - promptflow defines exact micro-steps
+    - agent jumps ahead or batches steps together
+    - stop conditions are bypassed
+    - validation occurs only in final prose rather than after each required artifact
+  countermeasure: Treat promptflow steps as binding execution constraints; hold at the first missed read, validation, stop condition, or target lock.
+  evidence_refs:
+    - OpenClaw/07_finalopenclawsystem/docs/working/META_DETECTIVE_WATCHDOG_QA_HYGIENE_EXECUTION_PLAN.md
+  scores:
+    score_scale: 1-100
+    EVD: 96
+    IMP: 98
+    RSK: 95
+  owner: meta_detective
+  validator: special_ops__hygiene_clean
+  review_due: 2026-07-25
+```
